Package no.uib.prideconverter.gui

Class Summary
ComboBoxInputDialog A dialog where the user can input the name of the new element to add to the combo box.
DataBaseDetails This frame handles the database connection to the ms_lims database.
DataFileSelection This frame handles the selection of the data files to be converted for dataformats with only on file per spectrum + identification.
DataFileSelectionTPP This frame handles the selection of the data files to be converted for TPP data sets (Peptide-/ProteinProphet).
DataFileSelectionTwoFileTypes This frame handles the selection of the data files to be converted for dataformats with two files, e.g., Spectrum Mill or Sequest.
DataSourceSelection This frame handles the selection of the dataformat to be converted.
ExperimentProperties This frame handles the experiment information (title and label) plus the contact and reference details.
HelpWindow A window used to display help text in html format.
Instrument This frame handles the information about the instrument (source, detector analyzers and processing methods).
ModificationMapping A dialog that lets the user map detected modifications to PSI-MOD CV terms.
NewAnalyzer A dialog for inserting information about an analyzer.
NewContact A dialog for inserting information about a contact.
NewProtocolStep A dialog where information about a protocol can be inserted.
NewReference A dialog to insert information about a reference.
NewSample A dialog where information about a sample can be inserted.
NewUserParameter A dialog for inserting user defined parameters.
OLSDialog A dialog for interacting with the Ontology Lookup Service OLS (http://www.ebi.ac.uk/ontology-lookup/).
OutputDetails This frame handles the final step in the wizard and deal with selecting the output folder and submitting the data to PRIDE.
ProgressDialog A dialog for showing information about the progress.
ProjectSelection A frame that lets the user select one or more ms_lims projects to convert into PRIDE XML.
ProteinIsoforms This dialog provides the user with three different alternatives for handeling the protein isoforms: (i) always select the first one, (ii) manual selection, or (iii) by providing a list of peptide to protein matches.
ProteinIsoFormSelection This dialog lets you choose between a different protein isoforms.
ProtocolDetails A frame where information about the protocol used can be inserted.
SampleDetails A frame where information about the samples can be inserted.
SpectraSelectionNoIdentifications This frame handles the spectra selection for all the data formats that are without identifications (e.g. pkl, dat, mgf).
SpectraSelectionWithIdentifications This frame handles the spectra selection for all the dataformats with identifications (e.g., X!
UserParameters A frame where user defined parameters can be added.
